links.title: J.B. Hunt Slides on Third-Quarter Earnings Miss
links.description: J.B. Hunt Transport Services was falling Friday after the trucking company missed Wall Street's third-quarter earnings estimates. Shares of the Lowell, Ark.-based company were off 6.2% to $133 in premarket trading. J.B. Hunt reported net income of $125.5 million, or $1.18 a share, down from $118.4 million, or $1.10 a share, a year ago, and below FactSet's call for earnings of $1.30.
